<div style="width:100vw; text-align: center; margin: 0 auto;">
	<h1 style="font-size: 50px; margin-top: 40px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;">when the bra fit</h1>
	<p style="margin:20px auto; font-size: 16px; width: 80%; letter-spacing: 1px;">
		When you're wearing your best fit, you'll feel more comfortable, confident, and yes, sexy! Here are a few tips to finding the right bra.<br>
		FYI : If DIY is not your thing, visit a store for a personalized fitting with a Victoria's Secret Bra Fit Expert.
	</p>
</div>


<div style="height: auto; overflow: inherit;">
	<div>
		<div style="min-width: 30%; max-width: 30%; margin-left: 20%; float: left; height: auto; overflow: visible;">
			<img src="../image/main/talkPic1.jpg">
		</div>
		
		<div style="float:left; max-width:20%; margin-left: 50px;">
			<div style="height:100px;">&nbsp</div>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Fasten your band on the middle hook so it sits comfortably level on your back & parallel to the floor.</p>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● If it digs in, try a looser hook. Still tight? Try a larger band & smaller cup size.</p>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Rides up? Try a tighter hook or go down a band size & up a cup size (if needed).</p>
		
			<div>
				<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; font-size: 40px; line-height: 45.6px; letter-spacing: .96px; margin-bottom: 9.6px;">Sport Bra Tip</h3>
				<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px;">● Your sport bra band should feel snug<br>
					around your rib cage, but not tight.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	
	<div>
		<div style="min-width: 30%; max-width: 30%; margin-left: 25%; float: left;  padding-right: 100px; height: auto; overflow: visible;">
			<div style="height:100px;">&nbsp</div>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Cups should fit smoothly, leaving no space between you & your bra.</p>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● If you are spilling over, go up a cup size.</p>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Cups gaping? Go down a size.</p>
			<div>
				<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; font-size: 40px; line-height: 45.6px; letter-spacing: .96px; margin-bottom: 9.6px;">Sport Bra Tip</h3>
				<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px;">● Your bra cup size will be the same for your sport bra.<br>
					around your rib cage, but not tight.</p>
			</div>
			
		</div>
		
		<div style="float:left; max-width:20%;">
			<img src="../image/main/talkPic2.jpg">
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<div>
		<div style="min-width: 30%; max-width: 30%; margin-left: 20%; float: left; height: auto; overflow: visible;">
			<img src="../image/main/talkPic3.jpg">
		</div>
		
		<div style="float:left; max-width:20%; margin-left: 50px;">
			<div style="height:100px;">&nbsp</div>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Most of the support comes from the band. Your straps should be tight enough to stay in place and keep your bra cups from gaping, but they should never dig into your shoulders.</p>
			<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px; padding-bottom: 15px;">● Try this trick: Drop your straps off your shoulders. If your bra stays put, you've got the right fit.</p>
		
			<div>
				<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; font-size: 40px; line-height: 45.6px; letter-spacing: .96px; margin-bottom: 9.6px;">Sport Bra Tip</h3>
				<p style="font-size: 16.8px; line-height: 21.6px; letter-spacing: 1.26px; margin-top: -4.8px;">● The straps of your sport bra should feel secure(with no slipping or digging in)to best minimize bounce.<br>
					around your rib cage, but not tight.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
	
